16/11/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska President Dragan Cavic said Friday (14 November) that Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic's apology was a step towards reconciliation. On Thursday, Marovic delivered his country's official apologies to the people of BiH for repression carried out during the 1992-1995 war. The Bosniak member of BiH presidency, Sulejman Tihic, also welcomed the move, saying it contributed to a better understanding and improved relations between the two countries. (FENA, HINA, TV Hayat - 14/11/03)
